Review: I was quite literally breath-taken at how beautiful the animation was, and how emotionally impactful some of the first-person POV shots were. I think I’ll be returning to theaters to watch this again before it leaves.
Best concert I’ve ever been to, and I didn’t even go

Napoleon suffers under the weight of its own realism. War is horrifying, pointless, and inflicted upon masses by egotistical men. But, we already knew that… so, why? Ultimately, it feels like Ridley Scott had no point of view on the subject. A few breathtaking shots and solid performances, unfortunately, don’t save this from being a slow-paced, mediocre movie with nothing to say.

Review: Dhont reels us in with a beautiful childhood friendship that is so fascinating and heartwarming, until he rips it out from under us with almost no context less than halfway through the runtime.The decision to kill-off Remi — a child whose character was never really explored, and whose only function is to experience homophobia and then die — is emotionally manipulative. It’s queer trauma exploitation to the maximum.The film does absolutely zero work to explore the grief of survivors…
